content:
The Inactive User Freezing feature increases sandbox security by freezing users in a Developer or Developer Pro sandbox within the first 60 days based on the time the user was created. This feature can’t be disabled.

Where: This change applies to Developer and Developer Pro sandboxes.

When: This feature is available on a rolling basis starting in July 2024.

Who: Any user who hasn’t logged in to an existing or newly created, cloned, or refreshed Developer or Developer Pro sandbox within the first 60 days is frozen.

How: This process runs automatically. You can provide access to frozen users by unfreezing their user accounts.
title: Increase Sandbox Security
